<section class="about_outer outer">
    <div class="about about_inner inner">
        <h2 class="section_title about_title">
            About me
        </h2>
        <p class="about_desc">
            I’m a graphic designer and frontend developer focused on building clean, purposeful digital experiences. I work at the intersection of visual design and implementation, which means I don’t just design how things look—I think about how they work, scale, and ship. <br/><br/>

With several years of hands-on experience across graphic design, motion graphics, digital art, and web design, I’ve developed a strong command of typography, color systems, layout, and visual hierarchy. I approach design with a minimalist mindset: reduce noise, highlight intent, and let the work breathe.<br/><br/>

On the web side, I design and build responsive, performance-conscious websites that translate design decisions into production-ready code. This allows for tighter feedback loops, fewer handoff issues, and designs that hold up in real-world usage.<br/><br/>

I value clarity, consistency, and thoughtful detail. Whether I’m designing a brand asset, crafting an interface, or building a frontend, my goal is always the same: create work that feels intentional, usable, and refined.<br/><br/>

I’m always learning, iterating, and improving—and I enjoy collaborating with teams and clients who care about quality and long-term impact.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
